title: Latest Sun Sentinel Girls Volleyball Results (Oct. 14)
text:
Plenty of Broward and Palm Beach volleyball matches
Broward
Brook Bauer and Kaylie McHugh helped lead St. Thomas Aquinas to its third-consecutive BCAA Big 8 Tournament championship on Wednesday.
With a 25-16, 25-17 win against Cypress Bay in the semifinals earlier in the day, the Raiders (23-2) defeated Cardinal Gibbons 25-20, 25-13 in the finals.
Junior Allison Marble led the Raiders in that win over Gibbons with eight kills, five digs and four points. Junior Emma Dixon was the top-performer in the win over the Lightning, totaling five points, four kills and three digs.
In the loss for Gibbons in the championship match, the Chiefs (15-5) got strong performances out of Daniella Molinari and Kassie Akouri.
Molinari had a team-high five kills, while Akouri led the way with nine assists.
Bauer and McHugh played key roles throughout the three-match tournament, in which the Raiders never dropped a set.
Bauer had a team-high 24 points and 20 kills. The junior also added 19 digs, six aces and three blocks.
McHugh led the Raiders with 30 digs in those three matches. The senior also had eight points, six assists and a pair of aces.
St. Thomas defeated West Broward on Tuesday to advance in the semifinals with scores of 25-14, 25-16.
